reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 14, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars So grateful to have found this notebook!
reviews.reviewText: The French always have the highest quality paper, it seems. The paper is light though surprisingly, no ink bleeds through -- I don't know how they achieve this feat but it is wonderful. I put the wire spiral up above when I write -- this way left-handed and right-handed persons can write without bumping arms against the wire. Colors come out crisply against the paper -- which is a light cream color. I wouldn't mind a brighter white at some point but this is just fine. Best of all, the grids themselves are very light. Light enough not to be seen through the ink but dark enough to be visible. Perfection, and thank you!
